body:
Go requires a `return` statement (with or without arguments) at the end of the function when the function has named return parameters:

    import "golang.org/x/sys/unix"

    func FreeSpace() (total int, err error) {
      var stat unix.Statfs_t

      err = unix.Statfs("/", &stat)
      if err != nil {
        // same as return total, err
        return
      }

      total = int(stat.Bavail * uint64(stat.Bsize))

      // same as return total, err
      return
    }

I'd like to propose to adjust the language spec so that the `return` at the very end of the function can be omitted. Any objections?
